The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Sept. 19: Bengal will house the second Indian Institute of Pharmaceuticals Research and Education after Punjab. 

 Chemicals and ferti- liser minister Ram Vilas Paswan has written to Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee agreeing to set up a branch of the institute here. A plot near Kalya-ni has been identified for the Rs 100-crore project. 

 Calcutta: The chief minister has drawn the Planning Commissions attention to inadequate funds provided under the urban renewal mission. Delhi will review allocations in October.

 Calcutta: State chief secretary A.K. Deb and home secretary P.R. Ray met top BSF and IB officers on Tuesday. They discussed security along the Bangladesh border.




